node.text: Sure, getting to the gym for an hour a day is an admirable commitment. But you want to know why it’s not nearly as hard as eating right? Because it’s only 1 HOUR a day! Good nutrition requires a dedicated effort for the other 23 hours of the day. Sure, even if you throw in 7-8 hours of sleep you still have to get it right for 15 hours. It’s not easy. But then again, nothing worth having ever comes easy. #nutrition #eatingainteasy #burnfat #diet #athleanx #teamathlean #jeffcavaliere

node.text: 10 minutes. 2 options. One heavier, one lighter. Pick your poison! Do this one at home or the gym. Equipment requirements are minimal (either a single resistance band or one pair of dumbbells). You can either train long or you can train hard, but you can’t do both. Experience that first hand here. Let the gains begin!! #biceps #bicepworkout #gains #armworkout #muscle #sleevebuster #teamathlean #jeffcavaliere #athleanx

node.text: People often think that I’d advocate little to no cheat meals if you want to be lean. Not at all. Remember, “lean” is a relative term and appropriately has a very broad definition. Some define it as “having visible abs”. Others define it as having face veins that run along side your eye socket (ummm, I swear that’s one I wish I could change!) The fact is, you can look damn good at much higher body fat levels than you might think. I covered that thought and more in this recent sit down with @therealbrianrose on his London Real podcast. If you haven’t already checked it out you can see it on londonreal.tv #podcast #cheatmeals #bodyfat #ripped #consistency #teamathlean #nutrition #jeffcavaliere #athleanx

node.text: This Recliner Tuck is Anti-extension ab work at its finest. The key is to sit back into posterior tilt as you recline. Go slow. Stay controlled. Your body will want to throw you into extension or anterior pelvic tilt as you approach the bottom (or your ab strength limits - whichever comes first!) Don’t let it! Easy to scale this exercise too. Use a lighter plate or no plate if you’re just starting out and extend the plate less up and certainly less back behind you if you are less advanced. Make the modifications needed to fit your abilities and give it a shot! Your abs will light up like an arsonist in a firework factory! That’s pretty lit 🔥 #abs #coreworkout #core #control #sixpack #teamathlean #jeffcavaliere #athleanx

node.text: Here’s a solid one for your next back or pull day. The underhand “v” bar row is similar to the dead row I’ve shared here before or the classic Yates Row from the barbell underhand row variation the great Dorian Yates preferred. No need for a landmine setup in the corner of the gym, just use your deadlift bar. You did deadlift didn’t you?!? Obviously this works best with handled plates. If the weight is on the light side you may be able to grip the edges or a plate if you’ve got strong fingers. Definitely one you’re going to want to try the next time you pull! Lat the gains begin... #rows #backday #biceps #pullday #lats #backworkout #athleanx #teamathlean #jeffcavaliere

node.text:
Looking for a jolt to your growth? Simply changing the starting position of an exercise (without having to change the exercise itself) is plenty of novel stimulus to push the pedal on your gains!! 

For instance, on this spider curl...

Do you almost always start from the bottom? If so, switch it up and start with the biceps in full contraction AND go on arm at a time! This combo will dramatically increase the time under peak tension for the biceps vs its bottom up version. 

If extraordinary muscle pain and discomfort sounds like the perfect end to a set to you (you sick bastard you!) then finish the set up with some bilateral reps to light that biceps bonfire! Let the gains begin! #biceps #changetherange #topdown #size #gains #theyregonnapop #athleanx #teamathlean #jeffcavaliere

node.text: This is one of my favorite ways to row. The hyperextension engages the lumbar paraspinals first, setting up the stability we all need on any bent row. From there, I perform an alternating rep of a row. By doing this one arm at a time I feel as if I have a much better ability to get the arm behind the body into solid extension (“touch the elbow to the spine” as my cue!). This also prolongs the time under tension of the entire rep, causing the low back to have to maintain that initial stability throughout. Give it a shot! I promise you’ll love the way this feels, and more so, the results it delivers!! #rowrowrowyourback #hyperrows #backworkout #lats #dumbbells #gains #jeffcavaliere #teamathlean #athleanx

node.text: I love this Crush Grip Pressout combo as a brutal shoulder or push day finisher! Don’t just hold the dumbbell, squeeze the living sh*t out of it with both hands! This will engage the chest and front delts isometrically. From there, angle press out to each side to better hit the middle delt and press straight out for more front delts. Once you reach fatigue, grip it even tighter and rip out a few more brutal reps pressing up overhead. One to three rounds will get the job done! Give it a try and let me know how you like it!! Let the gains begin my friend... #delts #shoulderworkout #finisher #bouldershoulders #3ddelts #burnout #teamathlean #jeffcavaliere #athleanx

Have a love hate relationship with leg training? It certainly can take a lot out of you if you bring the same intensity to it that you do international chest day!! But here’s some advice. Try and make it even more challenging than it is right now for you and I promise your body will respond quickly. 

“Seek the Suck” is what I like to say.

Ask yourself “how can I make what I’m doing even more miserable than it already is?” 

I’m glad you asked!

Here’s two variations of my favorite reverse barbell lunge that no doubt suck more than the typical barbell lunge (and are rightfully rewarding at the same time). The 1.5 rep version is especially brutal while the close footed squat / lunge combo is no walk in the park either. Incorporate either of them as a matter of fact and I would bet you actually might pass on that walk in the park (or even much walking anywhere for that matter for the next day or two!) #legday #legs #seekthesuck #burnout #quads #glutes #teamathlean #jeffcavaliere #athleanx
